## Pre-Registration Deviations Documented

Per section 13 of `PREREGISTRATION.md`, the following deviations are formally documented:

1. **Llama 3.3 70B comparator excluded from primary analysis.** Persistent connection-level instability via Groq prevented a reliable full comparator dataset (67 of 376 attempted calls successful). Retained as exploratory feasibility data only.
2. **Model version: GPT-5 -> GPT-5.4.** Pre-registration specified the model class; GPT-5.4 was the current frontier OpenAI version at execution time.
3. **Claude Opus 4.7 temperature parameter not accepted.** API-level constraint; documented and confirmed near-deterministic behavior empirically (90.4% baseline unanimity).
4. **Temperature changed from pre-registered 0.2 to 0 for Gemini and GPT-5.4.** PI methodological concern that nonzero temperature contaminates flip-rate measurement; rerun completed April 24-25, 2026; rerun confirmed primary outcome was meaningfully understated for Gemini 2.5 Pro at temperature 0.2 (4.33% -> 8.34%) but not for GPT-5.4 (3.46% -> 3.61%).

